The '''Teatro Metastasio''' is a theatre located in [[Prato]], [[Italy]]. Designed by architect [[Luigi De Cambray Digny]], construction of the theatre began in March 1829. The inaugural performance of theatre was of [[Gioachino Rossini]]'s ''[[Aureliano in Palmira]]'' on 8 October 1830. It remains the city of Prato's main venue for [[opera]]s, [[Play (theatre)|play]]s, and concerts.
